    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen two plugins specify the same name the second one cannot be installed. For example:\n\n`pluginA/nvim`\n`pluginB/nvim`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nCreate a config with these two lines.\n\n```lua\nvim.pack.add({\n\t{ src = \"https://github.com/catppuccin/nvim\" },\n\t{ src = \"https://github.com/ember-theme/nvim\" },\n})\n```\n\nHere's the output from nvim:\n```\nError in /home/zward/dots/nvim/.config/nvim/init.lua:\nE5113: Lua chunk: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua:439: Conflicting `src` for `nvim`:\nhttps://github.com/catppuccin/nvim\nhttps://github.com/ember-theme/nvim\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'error'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua:439: in function 'normalize_plugs'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua:1005: in function 'add'\n        /home/zward/dots/nvim/.config/nvim/init.lua:1: in main chunk\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThat both plugins should be installed.\n\nCurrently in the directory where the plugins are stored only the first one gets loaded and it's stored in a directory called `nvim`. So in theory having them in a directory like `catppuccin.nvim` and `ember-theme.nvim` would avoid this conflict.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nCachyOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.17.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
